Date:   Sat May 9 15:52:36 2026 +0700

    feat(1.17): implement CLI sdlc scan + sdlc status + accessibility flags

    - Add `sdlc scan`: thin CLI wrapper over engine.scanner.scan that writes
      state.json atomically and appends a scan_completed journal entry (AC1).
    - Add `sdlc status`: read-only resume card with phase name, last-updated
      timestamp from journal, and suggested-next-action stub (AC2).
    - Expand cli/output.py with echo, emit_json, emit_error, make_console,
      is_no_color_active (AC5).
    - Wire global --no-color and --json flags in cli/main.py root callback;
      register scan + status subcommands (AC6).
    - Honor NO_COLOR env var per no-color.org standard; add to ENV_EXACT_ALLOWLIST.
    - Add rich>=13,<15 as direct dependency.
    - Add state_to_canonical_bytes() to state/__init__.py as shared serializer.
    - Author ADR-020; update docs/decisions/index.md and cli-module codemap.
    - Add 38 targeted unit tests (scan, status, output, runtime-import validator)
      bringing total coverage 81% → 94% (gate: fail_under=90).
    - All 816 tests pass; all 16 pre-commit hooks green.

    Closes Story 1.17 (status: review).

